{"body": "The API link you're checking is related to the current stable version, 3.2.x, which has support for both Ruby 1.8 and 1.9, so the docs use the `=>` hash style. If you check the [edge guides for that](http://edgeapi.rubyonrails.org/classes/ActionMailer/Base.html), you'll see they use the new style hash, 1.9+.\r\n\r\nAnyway, both are just hash definitions, there's no real difference in the final result of the `default` call. Thanks!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14754935", "created_at": "2013-03-12T02:12:43Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9673#issuecomment-14754935", "updated_at": "2013-03-12T02:12:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9673, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e78abd3543c1510095b8"}, "id": 14754935, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rail